§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ A ❬real linear transformation❭ is a function $f: 𝗥^n → 𝗥^m$
    satisfying
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ f(αx + βy) = αf(x) + βf(y) \quad \text{for all } x, y
        ∈ 𝗥^n \text{ and } α, β ∈ 𝗥 ⦉
    ⦉⦉

  ‖ Equivalently, $f$ is (a) ❬homogenous❭ $f(αx) = αf(x)$ and
    (b) ❬additive❭ $f(x + y)= f(x) + f(y)$. ⦉
